						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying near Paravastu Raṅgāchārya's house in the same village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra Nārasiṁhadēva: Year 15: Śaka 1172 = 1249-50 A.D. (1234—35-A.D. ?)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> called <hi rend="italic">Śanivāra-maṇḍapa</hi> to the temple of Karumāṇi[k*]ka-Āḻvār at [Viśā]khapaṭṭiṉam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kulōttuṅgaśōḻa-paṭṭaṇam by a merchant who was a native of Pandalāyini-kkollam.</p>						

						</summary>
